<bug>
    <id>16717</id>
    <title>HTTPS FBML canvas shows blank dashboard</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Created an attachment (id=4244)
Normal index page of dashboard</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When our users try to access application dashboard with the https://apps.facebook.com/payvment_ they see a blank page instead of the normal index page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">http://apps.facebook.com/payvment works fine.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">We have a valid SSL certificate.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">The Tab URL with our attached application displays the storefront as it should ; on any user s Facebook fan page_ access using https:// works as it should.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">We ve reproduced this on both our production and development application.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">To reproduce the error_
search for Payvment E-Commerce Storefront application.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">Install the application while logged in the Facebook account
After a successful install_ try accessing http://apps.facebook.com/payvment
with https://apps.facebook.com/payvment instead.</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.3">The index page will be blank.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">This blank dashboard page error began on 2011-04-13 10:15pm
We ve made no changes to our code or configurations since then.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">We found a similar bug on the Facebook developers page which may or may not be related.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">http://bugs.developers.facebook.net/show_bug.cgi?id=14833</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
